<br>
Should the man be arrested? Nope. Just my opinion.<br>
<br>
The question that isn't being asked is this: Is the man and his family better or worse off by his drug use? I think unquestionably the man and his family are worse off. Therefore rather than arrest him maybe gently tell him his money and time is better spent on his family rather than getting high.<br>
<br>
Other drugs came up and it was mentioned herion and cocaine don't have casual users - very true. Getting high everyday, twice a day everyday is not casual either. Think it is casual? Get the man to quit for 90 days. $5 says the man can't.<br>
<br>
Think his family isn't hurt? Children will always suprise you with their knowledge and perception. As his children grow they will figure what Dad does on his twice daily trips out behind the house. How does this man tell his children that they shouldn't drop acid at 15? Smoke crack? He has lost the morale high ground with his children, he can no longer lead by example. I am sure his kids will look to him as a role model - they will expect drug use to be normal and common.<br>
<br>
How about the money? I haven't smoked in a long time, but getting high twice a day everyday has a price. A cash price. Nobody can tell me that the money couldn't be better spent. Buy his kids a bike, a catcher's glove, an art pad... anything. Buy his wife a dozen roses and nibble on her neck.<br>
<br>
And lastly it is illegal. What happens if he is caught? What happens if the police do press charges? What happens to the man and his family now? How does his wife tell his kids &quot;Dad is in jail&quot;? How does he tell his boss he missed the last three days because he was in jail for an unfair law? Does he lose his job? <br>
<br>
Is it worth it? Is he better off? His family?<br>
<br>
I don't think so. Just my opinion. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center>
